                 TOPIC 1 â€” TWO POINTERS
            â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â•â• -->
            <div class="topic-card" id="tp1">
                <div class="topic-header">
                    <div class="topic-num">01</div>
                    <div style="flex:1">
                        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap">
                            <div class="topic-title">Two Pointers</div>
                            <span class="tier-badge tier-T1">Foundation</span>
                            <span class="topic-type">Technique</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="topic-meta">54 problems Â· sorted array, linked list, string</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-body">
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Why It Matters:</strong> Tests ability to eliminate search space using invariants. O(n) solutions to O(nÂ²) problems demonstrate insight, not brute force.</div>
                    <div class="core-box"><strong>Core Idea:</strong> Maintain lo/hi (or slow/fast) pointers. Decide which to move based on a monotone condition. The invariant â€” what you prove about the space between pointers â€” IS the algorithm.</div>

