                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Why It Matters:</strong> Binary search is the canonical O(log n) technique. Every FAANG interview expects it on sorted arrays, rotated arrays, and â€” critically â€” on the answer space itself (binary search on value, not index).</div>
                    <div class="core-box"><strong>Core Idea:</strong> Maintain invariant: answer is always in [lo, hi]. Choose mid; decide which half to discard based on a monotone predicate. Template: lo=0, hi=n-1; while(loâ‰¤hi); always shrink the search space.</div>

