                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Why It Matters:</strong> Converts O(nÂ²) brute-force subarray enumeration into O(n) single-pass solutions by maintaining a live window [left, right] updated incrementally. The "aha" of recognizing when the window should shrink is a genuine test of algorithmic intuition.</div>
                    <div class="core-box"><strong>Core Idea:</strong> The window always represents a valid/optimal range. Instead of recomputing from scratch, add one element at right and remove one at left. The invariant is what makes the window valid â€” if you can't define it, the technique doesn't apply.</div>

