                    <div class="sec-title">Pattern Recognition Triggers</div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Linguistic Triggers (keywords in problem statement):</strong><br>
                        â€¢ "merge all overlapping intervals" â†’ Classic merge; sort by start, greedy extend<br>
                        â€¢ "minimum number of rooms / machines / conference halls" â†’ Count max simultaneous active intervals; sweep-line or min-heap<br>
                        â€¢ "non-overlapping" or "no two intervals overlap" â†’ Either removal (greedy) or weighted selection (DP)<br>
                        â€¢ "free time / available slots / gaps" â†’ Merge first, enumerate gaps between merged blocks<br>
                        â€¢ "insert â€¦ into sorted list of intervals" â†’ Three-phase walk (before, overlap, after)
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Structural Triggers (shape of input/output):</strong><br>
                        â€¢ Input is <code>int[][] intervals</code> or <code>List&lt;List&lt;Integer&gt;&gt;</code> of [start, end] pairs â†’ Almost always an interval problem<br>
                        â€¢ Output is a list of intervals â†’ Almost certainly merge or insert variant<br>
                        â€¢ Output is a single integer count where input is intervals â†’ Sweep-line / difference array
                    </div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Constraint Triggers (N and value ranges):</strong><br>
                        â€¢ N â‰¤ 10âµ and values up to 10â¹ â†’ Coordinate compression required; cannot use plain array for difference array<br>
                        â€¢ N â‰¤ 10âµ and online queries â†’ TreeMap / sorted set, not re-sort every time
