                    </div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Red Flags / Common Mistakes</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 1] Initialising prefix array of size n instead of n+1</strong> â€” Without the sentinel prefix[0] = 0, you cannot represent the subarray starting at index 0. Every range query is off by one. <em>Correct model:</em> "prefix[i] = sum of first i elements; prefix[0] = 0 always."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 2] Using hash map for inequality conditions (â‰¥ k, â‰¤ k)</strong> â€” Hash maps only resolve exact equality. <em>Correct model:</em> "Inequality requires a sorted structure â€” deque, BIT, or merge sort."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 2] Not initialising freq[0] = 1 before the loop</strong> â€” This misses subarrays that start from index 0. A subarray [0..j] has sum = prefix[j] âˆ’ 0 = prefix[j]. <em>Correct model:</em> "The empty prefix (before index 0) is a valid left boundary."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 3] Confusing difference array direction</strong> â€” Applying diff[l]+=v, diff[r]-=v (forgetting the +1 on r) when the interval is inclusive [l,r] subtracts one position too early, corrupting index r. <em>Correct model:</em> "Subtract at the position AFTER the endpoint â€” prefix sum must carry the value through r."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 4] Trying to apply prefix sums to MAX/MIN queries</strong> â€” A candidate drilled on prefix sums will attempt prefix_max[j] âˆ’ prefix_max[i] for range max. Algebraically unsound. <em>Correct model:</em> "Only operations with an inverse (+, XOR, Ã—) support the prefix trick. Max/min have no inverse."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 5] Rebuilding static prefix after each update (O(n) per update)</strong> â€” For n=10âµ and q=10âµ updates, this is 10Â¹â° ops. <em>Correct model:</em> "Any update invalidates all subsequent prefix values â€” you need a data structure designed for dynamic prefixes."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 3] Computing 2D prefix sum in wrong order (column before row)</strong> â€” Building prefix[i][j] requires prefix[i-1][j], prefix[i][j-1], prefix[i-1][j-1] all finalised. <em>Correct model:</em> "Always iterate rows outer, columns inner â€” or verify all dependencies are filled before use."</div>

