                        <strong>7. Permutations with duplicates</strong> â€” Stage 2 Â· O(n!/duplicates!) Â· sort + used array + dup check Â· <em>New idea:</em> skip if nums[i]==nums[iâˆ’1] AND used[iâˆ’1]==False (same-level skip)<br>
                        <strong>8. Palindrome partitioning</strong> â€” Stage 3 Â· O(n Â· 2â¿) Â· recursion + palindrome precomputation Â· <em>New idea:</em> at each position, try all valid prefix lengths; validity = palindrome check<br>
                        <strong>9. Word search on grid</strong> â€” Stage 3 Â· O(nÂ·mÂ·4^L) Â· DFS on grid with visited marking Â· <em>New idea:</em> state is 2D grid position + word index; visited marking replaces used array<br>
                        <strong>10. N-Queens</strong> â€” Stage 3 Â· O(n!) Â· row-by-row with column/diagonal sets Â· <em>New idea:</em> constraint encoded as three sets (col, diag1, diag2); O(1) per placement<br>
                        <strong>11. Sudoku solver</strong> â€” Stage 3 Â· O(9^m) where m = empty cells Â· cell-by-cell with row/col/box sets Â· <em>New idea:</em> constraint propagation (only try digits missing from row+col+box)<br>
                        <strong>12. Graph colouring / m-colouring</strong> â€” Stage 3 Â· O(mâ¿) Â· vertex-by-vertex with adjacency check Â· <em>New idea:</em> constraint is graph-local (neighbours can't share colour)<br>
                        <strong>13. Exact cover / Algorithm X</strong> â€” Stage 4 Â· O(solution-dependent) Â· dancing links / recursive cover Â· <em>New idea:</em> problem reduces to covering all columns of a binary matrix exactly once<br>
                        <strong>14. Expression evaluation / operator insertion</strong> â€” Stage 4 Â· O(4^(nâˆ’1) Â· n) Â· recursion with running value Â· <em>New idea:</em> multiply requires tracking the last-added term to handle operator precedence<br>
                        <strong>15. Constraint satisfaction (CSP)</strong> â€” Stage 4 Â· varies Â· backtracking + forward checking + arc consistency Â· <em>New idea:</em> propagation before each choice reduces future domains<br>
                        <strong>16. Bitmask-pruned backtracking</strong> â€” Stage 5 Â· O(2â¿ Â· n) Â· bitmask state + memoisation Â· <em>New idea:</em> state compressed into bitmask; memoisation collapses identical subtrees<br>
                        <strong>17. Branch and bound</strong> â€” Stage 5 Â· exponential worst-case, fast in practice Â· upper bound + priority queue Â· <em>New idea:</em> prune branches where even the best possible completion can't beat current best<br>
