                    </div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Red Flags / Common Mistakes</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 1] Appending path reference instead of path copy</strong> â€” <code>result.append(path)</code> stores a reference to a list that will be mutated. All results become identical. <em>Correct model:</em> "I'm storing a snapshot â€” always path[:]."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 2] Skipping duplicates with i &gt; 0 instead of i &gt; start</strong> â€” Using i &gt; 0 skips elements at the beginning of deeper recursion levels, silently dropping valid combinations. <em>Correct model:</em> "Skip a duplicate only if it's at the SAME level â€” i &gt; start enforces same-level scope."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 3] Missing the undo step for grid problems</strong> â€” Marking visited=True but forgetting =False means cells remain blocked for sibling branches. Symptom: fewer results than expected. <em>Correct model:</em> "Every mutation before a recursive call must be reversed after it â€” no exceptions."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 4] Treating a counting problem as enumeration</strong> â€” "How many valid arrangements exist?" can sometimes be solved via DP without enumeration. Backtracking counts by generating every solution â€” exponential. <em>Correct model:</em> "If N &gt; 15, check for DP before backtracking."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 4] Not recognising a game-theory problem as backtracking</strong> â€” "Can player 1 guarantee a win?" is a minimax tree. Candidates try BFS or greedy. <em>Correct model:</em> "Optimal play = exhaustive game-tree search. A position is winning iff any child is losing for the opponent."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 5] Running backtracking without pruning on constraint problems</strong> â€” Unconstrained Sudoku is O(9^81) â€” effectively infinite. <em>Correct model:</em> "Constraint propagation is mandatory, not optional. Always narrow the choice set before recursing."</div>
                    <div class="warn-box">ðŸš© <strong>[Stage 5] Confusing "backtracking with memo" with DP</strong> â€” When you memoise backtrack(index, state), you have written top-down DP. Not recognising this signals incomplete mastery. <em>Correct model:</em> "Memoised backtracking IS DP. Name it correctly and explain the state definition."</div>

                    <div class="sec-title">Interviewer Follow-Up Questions</div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Stage 2 Follow-Ups (Constraint Mutations)</strong></div>
