                        <tr><td>7</td><td>"Your backtracking is O(n!). Can memoisation help here?"</td><td>Only if overlapping subproblems exist â€” same remaining set reached via different orderings. If state = bitmask of used elements, memo table has 2â¿ entries; total O(2â¿ Â· n).</td></tr>
                        <tr><td>8</td><td>"N = 20 and your bitmask DP is O(2Â²â° Â· 20) â‰ˆ 2Ã—10â·. What if N = 40?"</td><td>Meet in the middle: enumerate subsets of first 20 (2Â²â°) and last 20 (2Â²â°), then combine. Still exponential but halved exponent: O(2^(n/2)).</td></tr>
                        </tbody></table></div>
                    <div class="info-box"><strong>Beyond Stage 5 (Adversarial / Distributed)</strong></div>
                    <div class="tbl-wrap"><table>
